# Corn Salsa

## Ingredients
* 1 cup corn (Fresh>frozen>canned)
* 1 cup chopped tomatoes
* 1/4 red onion, diced
* 1 spicy pepper, seeded & diced
     * If we don't have a spicy pepper add cayenne instead
* Cilantro
* 1 lime, zested & juiced
* Salt & pepper to taste

## Instructions
* Saute corn over medium-high heat to get some color
* Add corn to a bowl with the rest of the ingredients, stir
* Tastes best an hour or two after combining. Keeps for a day or two, just need to drain extra liquid
